version_description: Specific, timed chords and lyrics, strumming patterns, performance and structure notes.
This song is tuned down a 1/2 step which I believe he does normally. Very simple musically.

The other version sounds good but it uses a Capo. Zac tunes 1/2 step down and I think you get a much fuller sound with more bottom end when it's played without the Capo. Plus, unlike the other version, this one has complete lyric coverage, adds chords the other missed, and includes the breaks and intro.
Acoustic Version with the Capo on 3rd Fret.
This is a very simple version yet accurate version of the chords of the song that Zac Brown of Zach Brown Band used for the 2011 Footloose film.
Chords for the studio version of the song, with a tab for the intro lick.

song_name: Standing On The Shoulder Of Giants
